  <summary>5/16/1997--Introduced.
Amends the Trade Act of 1974 to direct the United States Trade Representative (USTR) to, in addition to any other action considered appropriate and feasible, impose upon a country and its nationals conditions, limitations, and prohibitions on investment in the United States that are similar to those implemented by the country with respect to U.S. investment in such country.</summary>
